The party isn't marked red everywhere
In Hungary, the law defines exactly the holiday days and, around the holidays, it has become common to reorganise the working days whose number will decrease next year.
Holidays are not uniform in the EU and the United States either.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes national and state holidays and rest days.
Days of rest are often linked to religious festivals or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the new year, the last day of the year ending and the first day of the new year are also days of rest, the latter all the more so that the alarm clocks can rest quietly.
Moreover, in a year, we have in all eleven red-marked parties.
March 15 is a national celebration, in commemoration of the revolution of 1848, as on October 23, also which is the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20th, we celebrate the constitution of our state, May 1st is the labour festival and November 1st and 2nd, we remember the members of our family and our deceased friends.
In addition, we have two days at Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or even religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, according to the calendar, it has become common to reorganize working days in cases where there is only one working day left before or after the feast marked in red.
It is true that we pay the price of extended weekends by working or going to school the Saturday before extended weekends.
For many years, the Minister of Labour has been acting in special regulations on days of replacement for days prior to or following holidays.
The law extends to all employers and their employees, to civil servants and to persons working in the public service.
It does not apply, however, to service companies, institutions that rotate without interruption and in service, by virtue of their vocation, and also for days of rest.
This year, working days will be modified only around the end of the year holidays: from December 24, life stops almost throughout the country because according to experiences the majority of people do more hours or take holidays that they have saved for these purposes in order to spend the days between Christmas and New Year's Day at home.
Next year many parties fall in the middle or end of the week, so there will be fewer changes in working days compared to this year.
The schedule will be reorganized the first time around the work day to allow employees to stay home four days in a row.
Saturday, April 25 will be a day of work to have a day of rest on Friday, May 2.
Another change is scheduled for October 23rd: Saturday, October 18th will be a working day replacing Friday, 24.
On the other hand, next year, the end of the year is announced under the sign of the holidays because from December 24, everyone will take a non-stop break even if the New Year's Day falls on a Wednesday.
