In parallel to its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the Congress' vote on the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim of its entry into force before the end of the year.
Representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by members of Parliament and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of the agencies to ensure that markets function effectively.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves modernising financial markets, as it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial advisory services for both specialized social reasons and for natural or legal persons and will create a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial advisory companies (FIAs), which merge securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
